So the different definitions that we brought is co-housing.

222
00:32:38,743 --> 00:32:44,988
There was co-living that then we, last year, we took out.

223
00:32:45,228 --> 00:32:51,173
But we just wanted to bring it in in case we want to understand better those differences.

224
00:32:52,594 --> 00:32:54,435
We have the existing dormitory.

225
00:32:54,455 --> 00:32:55,656
This was not updated.

226
00:32:55,776 --> 00:33:01,501
So to discuss if this needs to be updated, fraternity or sorority house and lodging house.

227
00:33:02,201 --> 00:33:06,463
So I'm going to read them so we have time to discuss all of them.

228
00:33:07,763 --> 00:33:23,209
So co-housing is a group of buildings in common ownership which include a combination of single unit, two unit or multi-unit buildings and one or more buildings with shared living spaces such as common room, library, dining room, kitchen, etc.

229
00:33:24,922 --> 00:33:37,184
Co-living is a building in which a group of residents pay rent to occupy a single unit with private bedrooms and shared living spaces, including cooking and sanitary facilities.

230
00:33:37,684 --> 00:33:42,685
Such residents have input over the selection of the other residents living in the housing unit.

231
00:33:44,145 --> 00:33:48,746
This at the moment, the one in blue, co-living, is not in your zoning.

232
00:33:49,986 --> 00:33:52,967
So just to, if we want to include it or not.

233
00:33:53,887 --> 00:34:14,673
Dormitory, as per your existing definition, any dwelling other than a sorority or fraternity house owned or controlled by an educational institution and occupied primarily as a place of temporary residence for persons who are employed or enrolled at the educational institution.

234
00:34:16,242 --> 00:34:24,264
Fraternity or sorority house, a dormitory in which, during the academic year, membership in fraternity or sorority is required as a condition to residence.

235
00:34:24,905 --> 00:34:41,890
Lodging house, a dwelling in which living space without individual kitchens and with or without kitchen privileges is designed, occupied, or intended for occupancy by or led for compensation to five or more lodgers, including a rooming house or boarding house.

236
00:34:42,370 --> 00:34:50,753
but not including a senior housing facility, hotel or motel, dormitory, fraternity or sorority house, or other building of any institutional or educational use.

237
00:34:52,473 --> 00:34:53,634
We can come back to this one.

238
00:34:55,935 --> 00:35:00,256
I know that there are some questions about dormitories, so we just wanted to bring the definitions in.

239
00:35:01,963 --> 00:35:06,564
The other definitions to review, they're not housing related, is the life science facility.

240
00:35:06,584 --> 00:35:15,627
It's a facility for study, testing, and development of products or services related to chemicals, drugs, or biological matter, and research and testing laboratory.

241
00:35:16,167 --> 00:35:25,310
Those facilities used primarily for research, development, and or testing of innovative information, concepts, methods, processes, materials, or products.

242
00:35:25,790 --> 00:35:30,572
This can include the design, development, and testing of biological, chemical, electrical, magnetic, mechanical,

243
00:35:31,072 --> 00:35:34,515
and or optical components in advance of product manufacturing.

244
00:35:34,915 --> 00:35:51,190
The accessory development, fabrication, and light manufacturing of prototypes or specialized machinery and devices integral to research or testing may be associated with these uses, but excluding laboratories categorized as level three or four by the National Institute for Health.

245
00:35:51,750 --> 00:35:58,113
So there are some life science that could be included in the research and testing lab.

246
00:35:58,574 --> 00:36:04,517
Sometimes as a marketing strategy, life science is placed in a different position.

247
00:36:05,097 --> 00:36:08,979
And that's why it's a lot of the time separated in a lot of the zonings.

248
00:36:10,059 --> 00:36:13,061
But just to, if we wanted to rethink about this.

249
00:36:15,298 --> 00:36:18,280
So then we go into the purpose.

250
00:36:19,020 --> 00:36:27,725
So the purpose of the Boston Avenue Neighborhood Corridor District is to allow a mix of uses, including residential, multifamily, and commercial, to meet the following needs.

251
00:36:28,305 --> 00:36:39,892
Wider variety of uses and building types to support jobs and economic development near established residential neighborhoods, providing options for living within walking distance of jobs, goods, and services.

252
00:36:40,712 --> 00:36:54,357
Flood transitions to and from the Chaff's University campus to allow integral approach to living, working, and learning along Boston Avenue from the Somerville line north of the Southern Street to the Somerville border at Ball Square.

253
00:36:55,198 --> 00:37:07,843
Mixed-use multifamily and commercial uses at a density to reinforce non-vehicular travel between the adjacent neighborhoods to the jobs, goods, and services within the Boston Avenue neighborhood corridor district.

254
00:37:09,110 --> 00:37:19,553
Development standards to provide landscape and height buffers from the new construction within the Boston Avenue neighborhood corridor district for the existing abutting neighborhoods.

255
00:37:22,794 --> 00:37:25,374
And then we go into the dimensional standards.

256
00:37:25,634 --> 00:37:26,815
We start with height.

257
