00:44:26,716 --> 00:44:30,178
So I think that's why I'm being reminded now.

323
00:44:30,198 --> 00:44:35,861
And my question was, so we've had removed co-living because it didn't seem to add anything.

324
00:44:35,981 --> 00:44:37,382
It's simply a rental apartment.

325
00:44:37,402 --> 00:44:37,983
There's really no...

326
00:44:38,703 --> 00:45:00,580
reason for it to be in there, but the reason why we originally talked about it was to make a distinction between a lodging house, which is where the landlord selects people who are living in the same apartment or same unit together, and people who choose to live in the same unit together because they're friends or, you know, they have something in common.

327
00:45:02,521 --> 00:45:07,045
So seeing that lodging house is anything more than four people

328
00:45:09,355 --> 00:45:12,297
but it doesn't say anything about whether those people are choosing to live together.

329
00:45:12,777 --> 00:45:22,923
Like I forgot that if we, I don't, I think I didn't realize that when we remove the co-living, then suddenly anyone, any five roommates suddenly become a lodging house.

330
00:45:24,884 --> 00:45:28,267
So I'm curious about that because I don't think that was our intention.

331
00:45:28,287 --> 00:45:35,491
I think the purpose of like discussing the co-living situation was to differentiate between these things and to sort of

332
00:45:38,177 --> 00:45:42,439
make it so that we could allow people who wanted to sort of live.

333
00:45:42,459 --> 00:45:46,701
I mean we have a lot of we have houses with five six bedrooms.

334
